user_prompt <- "
Access all URLs listed below. Return all mentions of the following topics:
- Regulatory action on live baitfish/minnows as fishing bait
- Regulatory action on the importation of invasive species
List all current/ongoing rulemaking initatives or informal discussions, identified in the list of links that I originally sent, on the topic of live baitfish.
Include *only* discussions or initiatives that have been active in the past month. If there are no such discussions within this time frame, do *not* simulate results - simply report that you did not find any hits.
In the case of webpages that include meeting agendas, follow the links to access the most recent agendas/minutes/information packets, and search that information. This might require following multiple links to find the most recent PDF or webpage with the meeting agenda or minutes.
For each "hit", return a short, three-sentence summary that includes the state, the key details of the discussion, and the source where I can manually find more information about that discussion.
user_prompt <- "
Access all URLs listed below. Return all mentions of the following topics:
- Regulatory action on live baitfish/minnows as fishing bait
- Regulatory action on the importation of invasive species
List all current/ongoing rulemaking initatives or informal discussions, identified in the list of links that I originally sent, on the topic of live baitfish.
Include *only* discussions or initiatives that have been active in the past month. If there are no such discussions within this time frame, do *not* simulate results - simply report that you did not find any hits.
In the case of webpages that include meeting agendas, follow the links to access the most recent agendas/minutes/information packets, and search that information. This might require following multiple links to find the most recent PDF or webpage with the meeting agenda or minutes.
For each hit, return a short, three-sentence summary that includes the state, the key details of the discussion, and the source where I can manually find more information about that discussion.
"
